 Nigeria has recorded 661 new cases of the Coronavirus According to a tweet from the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Saturday night, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in Nigeria is now 19,808, with 6,718 persons discharged. The breakdown of figures recorded according to states is as follows: Lagos-230 Rivers-127 Delta-83 FCT-60 Oyo-51 Edo-31 Bayelsa-27 Kaduna-25 Plateau-13 Ondo-6 Nasarawa-3 Ekiti-2 Kano-2 Borno-1 506 persons have so far lost their lives in Nigeria due to Coronavirus, the tweet said.  661 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-230Rivers-127Delta-83FCT-60Oyo-51Edo-31Bayelsa-27Kaduna-25Plateau-13Ondo-6Nasarawa-3Ekiti-2Kano-2Borno-1 19,808 confirmed6,718 discharged506 deaths pic.twitter.com/PH87IGyn5R â€” NCDC (@NCDCgov) June 20, 2020  